==Renaissance (2015)== {{Infobox Wrestling event |name=Renaissance (2015) |image= |caption= |promotion=[[Philippine Wrestling Revolution]] |date={{dts|2015|09|26}}<ref name="ren15pwr">{{cite web | url=http://www.pwrcentral.com/renaissance-2015-results/| title=Renaissance 2015|date=October 31, 2015| accessdate= August 24, 2016 | publisher= PWR Central}}</ref> |venue=Makati Square Arena |city=[[Makati|Makati City, Philippines]] |liveevent=y |event= Renaissance |lastevent=[[List of Philippine Wrestling Revolution events#PWR_Live|PWR Live]] |nextevent=[[List of Philippine Wrestling Revolution events#PWR_Live_2|PWR Live 2]] |lastevent2=[[List of Philippine Wrestling Revolution events#Renaissance_.282014.29|Renaissance (2014)]] |nextevent2=[[List of Philippine Wrestling Revolution events#Renaissance_.282016.29|Renaissance (2016)]] }} The PHX Championship tournament culminated during this event. This would be the last PWR show held at the Makati Square Arena.
Before the main event, comedian Stanley Chi hosted a ''Suplado Show'' in-ring segment, with Kanto Terror, then Mark D. Manalo and PWR General Manager Mr. Sy. {{Pro Wrestling results table |results=<ref name="ren15pwr" /><ref name="ren15w">{{cite web | url=http://www.wheninmanila.com/pwr-renaissance-lightning-strikes-twice-for-pwrs-second-renaissance-event/| title=PWR Renaissance – Lightning Strikes Twice For PWR’s Second Renaissance Event|date= September 29, 2015 | accessdate= August 24, 2016 | publisher= When in Manila}}</ref><ref name="ren15sh">{{cite web | url=http://www.smarkhenry.ph/2015/09/the-smark-henry-review-of-pwr.html| title=The Smark Henry Review of PWR Renaissance| date= September 30, 2015 | accessdate= August 24, 2016 | publisher= Smark Henry}}</ref> |pre1 = yes |match1="The Machine" Mavericc Knight defeated Vintendo |stip1=[[Professional wrestling match types#Singles matches|Singles match]] |pre2 = yes |match2=Mark D. Manalo defeated Jimmy Orellana |stip2=Singles match |match3=Fighters 4 Hire (Joey Bax and Miguel Rosales) defeated Dual Shock (Peter Versoza and SANDATA) |stip3=[[Professional wrestling match types#Series variations|2-out-of-3 falls]] [[Professional wrestling match types#Tag team matches|tag team match]] |match4=Mayhem Brannigan defeated Chris Panzer |stip4=PHX Championship tournament semi-final match Both men were attacked by Fighters 4 Hire afterwards. Brannigan wasn't able to advance to the final. |match5=John Sebastian defeated Bombay Suarez |stip5= [[Professional wrestling match types#No Holds Barred match|No Holds Barred match]] |match6="The Social Media Sinister" Ken Warren defeated Ralph Imabayashi |stip6=Tournament final for the PHX Championship |match7="Classical" Bryan Leo (c) defeated "The Senyorito" Jake de Leon and The Apocalypse |stip7=[[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|Three-way match]] for the PWR Championship }}
