==PWR Live: The ShawDown== {{Infobox Wrestling event |name=PWR Live: The ShawDown |image= |caption= |promotion=[[Philippine Wrestling Revolution]] |date={{dts|2016|07|30}}<ref name="livesdpwr">{{cite web | url=http://www.pwrcentral.com/pwr-live-the-shawdown/| title=PWR LIVE: The Shawdown|date=August 7, 2016| accessdate= November 14, 2016 | publisher= PWR Central}}</ref> |venue=500 Shaw Events Pavilion |city=[[Mandaluyong City| Mandaluyong City, Philippines]] |liveevent=y |event=PWR Live |lastevent=[[List of Philippine Wrestling Revolution events#Wrevolution X_.282016.29|Wrevolution X (2016)]] |nextevent=[[List of Philippine Wrestling Revolution events#Renaissance_.282016.29|Renaissance (2016)]] |lastevent2=[[List of Philippine Wrestling Revolution events#PWR Live: The Road to Wrevolution X|PWR Live: The Road to Wrevolution X]] |nextevent2=[[List of Philippine Wrestling Revolution events#PWR Live: Suplex Sunday|PWR Live: Suplex Sunday]] }} This was PWR's first event in [[Mandaluyong City]].
During the show, Rederick Mahaba hosted a ''Mahabang Usapan'' in-ring segment, with PWR Champion Jake de Leon, Ralph Imabayashi, John Sebastian, PHX Champion Main Maxx, and Peter Versoza as guests.
Crystal and Scarlett were scheduled to have a contract signing for a match at Renaissance, but Scarlett [http://www.smarkhenry.ph/2016/07/pwrs-scarlett-announces-her-retirement.html announced her retirement from wrestling] days before PWR Live. {{Pro Wrestling results table |results=<ref name="livesdpwr" /><ref name="livesdsh">{{cite web | url=http://www.smarkhenry.ph/2016/08/pwr-live-shawdown.html| title=PWR Live: The SHAWdown! Review|date=August 10, 2016| accessdate= November 14, 2016 | publisher= Smark Henry}}</ref> |pre1=yes |match1=The Network (James "Idol" Martinez, Chino Guinto and Bruno Bernardo) defeated Vintendo and Delirium (Dax Xaviera and Dan Ericson) |stip1=Six-man [[Professional wrestling match types#Tag team matches|tag team match]] |match2=Yohann Ollores (w/ Logan Ollores) defeated Mark D. Manalo (w/ Kanto Terror) |stip2=[[Professional wrestling match types#Singles matches|Singles match]] |match3=Rederick Mahaba defeated Ken Warren via count-out |stip3=Singles match |match4=Joey Bax defeated Mike Madrigal |stip4=Singles match |match5=Vlad Sinnsyk defeated Ralph Imabayashi |stip5=Singles match |match6=SANDATA versus "Classical" Bryan Leo ended in a no contest |stip6=Singles match Leo did not show up at the event. Chino Guinto confronted SANDATA instead. |match7=Martivo defeated Trabajador Tres |stip7=Singles match |match8=John Sebastian defeated The Apocalypse and Chris Panzer |stip8=[[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|Three-way match]] to determine the #1 contender to the PWR Championship Apocalypse was added to the match by the PWR Board of Directors. |match9=PWR Champion Jake de Leon defeated PHX Champion Main Maxx via DQ |stip9="Champion versus Champion" singles match }}
