Also, after The Apocalypse's victory in the All Out War Match, the PWR Board awarded him with the PWR All Out War Championship in recognition of his success in All Out War matches. {{Pro Wrestling results table |results=<ref name="bsbsh" /><ref name="bsbr">{{cite web |url=http://www.rappler.com/sports/by-sport/other-sports/176491-pwr-live-bakbakan-bayanihan-results |title='Beautiful' Billy Suede crowned PWR champion at 'Bakbakan sa Bayanihan'|date=July 23, 2017| accessdate= July 24, 2017 | publisher= Rappler}}</ref> |pre1=yes |match1=Brad Cruz defeated Trabajador Quatro |stip1=[[Professional wrestling match types#Singles matches|Singles match]] |pre2=yes |match2=Bolt def. Vintendo via DQ |stip2=Singles match |match3=The Apocalypse def. Trian dela Torre |stip3=[[Professional wrestling match types#Hardcore-based variations|All Out War Match]] |match4=Punk Dolls (Martivo and Robynn) def. The KakaiBros (Kh3Ndrick and Mh4rckie) |stip4=[[Professional wrestling match types#Tag team match|Tag team match]] |match5=Vlad Sinnsyk def. SANDATA |stip5=Singles match |match6=The YOLO Twins (Yohann and Logan Ollores) (c) def. The Network (James "Idol" Martinez and Alexander Belmonte III) |stip6=Tag team match for the PWR Tag Team Championship |match7=Dax Xaviera def. Ken Warren |stip7=Singles match |match8=Peter Versoza and John Sebastian versus Fighters 4 Hire (Joey Bax and Miguel Rosales) went to a no contest |stip8=Tag team match |match9=Ralph Imabayashi def. Jake de Leon |stip9=[[Professional wrestling match types#Last Man Standing match|"Matira Matibay"]] match |match10=[[Billy Suede|"Beautiful" Billy Suede]] def. Chris Panzer (c) |stip10=Singles match for the PWR Championship |}}
==PWR Live: Sugod!== {{Infobox Wrestling event |name=PWR Live: Sugod! |image= |caption= |promotion=[[Philippine Wrestling Revolution]] |date={{dts|2017|09|03}}<ref name="sugodsh">{{cite web |url=http://www.smarkhenry.ph/2017/09/live-results-pwr-live-sugod.html|title=[FULL RESULTS] PWR Live: Sugod!|date=September 3, 2017| accessdate= April 10, 2018 | publisher= Smark Henry}}</ref> |venue=Power Mac Center Spotlight |city=[[Makati City| Makati City, Philippines]] |liveevent=y |event=PWR Live |lastevent=[[List of Philippine Wrestling Revolution events#PWR Live: Resbak|PWR Live: Bakbakan sa Bayanihan]] |nextevent=[[List of Philippine Wrestling Revolution events#PWR Live: Oktoberplex|PWR Live: Oktoberplex]] |lastevent2=[[List of Philippine Wrestling Revolution events#PWR Live: Resbak|PWR Live: Bakbakan sa Bayanihan]] |nextevent2=[[List of Philippine Wrestling Revolution events#PWR Live: Oktoberplex|PWR Live: Oktoberplex]] }} This was PWR's first show at the Power Mac Center Spotlight in Makati City.
In the opening segment, John Sebastian revealed that he became a co-owner of PWR after buying 50% of the company. He then challenged Mr. Sy to a 5-on-5 elimination match at ''Vendetta''. If Mr. Sy's team loses, he would be fired as PWR General Manager. {{Pro Wrestling results table |results=<ref name="sugodsh" /><ref name="sugodr">{{cite web |url=https://www.rappler.com/sports/by-sport/other-sports/181633-pwr-live-sugod-results-review |title='PWR Live: Sugod!' review: Team up, step up|date=September 10, 2017| accessdate= April 10, 2018 | publisher= Rappler}}</ref> |pre1=yes |match1=The Revo-Ranger defeated Trabajador Quatro |stip1=[[Professional wrestling match types#Singles matches|Singles match]] |pre2=yes |match2=McKata def. Vintendo |stip2=Singles match |match3=Rederick Mahaba (w/ Ralph Imabayashi) def. Dax Xaviera |stip3=Singles match |match4=All Out War Champion The Apocalypse def. Brad Cruz |stip4=Non-title singles match |match5=Bolt def. Zayden Trudeau |stip5=Singles match |match6=Jake de Leon def. Vlad Sinnsyk |stip6=Singles match |match7=Peter Versoza def. Joey Bax |stip7=Singles match |match8=TDTxECX (Evan Carleaux and Trian dela Torre) def. The YOLO Twins (Yohann and Logan Ollores), Punk Dolls (Robynn and Martivo), and The KakaiBros (Kh3ndrick and Mh4rckie) |stip8=[[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|Fatal four-way]] [[Professional wrestling match types#Tag team match|tag team match]] to determine #1 contenders to the PWR Tag Team Championship |match9=Mike Madrigal (c) def. SANDATA |stip9=Singles match for the PHX Championship |match10=Chris Panzer def. [[Billy Suede|"Beautiful" Billy Suede]] (c) and Ralph Imabayashi (w/ Rederick Mahaba) |stip10=[[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|Triple threat match]] for the PWR Championship |}}
