==PWR Live: Holding Hands While Wrestling== {{Infobox Wrestling event |name=PWR Live: Holding Hands While Wrestling |image= |caption= |promotion=[[Philippine Wrestling Revolution]] |date={{dts|2018|02|11}}<ref name="hhwwsh18">{{cite web |url=http://www.smarkhenry.ph/2018/02/full-results-pwr-live-holding-hands.html|title=[FULL RESULTS] PWR Live: Holding Hands While Wrestling|date=February 11, 2018| accessdate= April 16, 2018 | publisher= Smark Henry}}</ref> |venue=Venue 142 Events Place |city=[[Quezon City|Quezon City, Philippines]] |liveevent=y |event=PWR Live |lastevent=[[List of Philippine Wrestling Revolution events#Vendetta (2017)|Vendetta (2017)]] |nextevent=[[List of Philippine Wrestling Revolution events#Path of Gold (2018)|Path of Gold (2018)]] |lastevent2=[[List of Philippine Wrestling Revolution events#PWR Live: Kingdom Come|PWR Live: Kingdom Come]] |nextevent2=PWR Live: Trapik }} The show started with a "Championship Celebration of Love and Respect" by Rederick Mahaba for the new PWR Champion, Ralph Imabayashi. It was interrupted by Miguel Rosales.
Before the match between The Network and the team of McKata and Brad Cruz, John Sebastian officiated a rap battle between James "Idol" Martinez and McKata, which Martinez won.
At the end of the tournament to determine the #1 contenders to the PWR Tag Team Championship, John Sebastian and Crystal inserted themselves into the title match at ''Path of Gold'', making it a triple threat match. {{Pro Wrestling results table |results=<ref name="hhwwsh18" /><ref name="hhwwr18">{{cite web |url=https://www.rappler.com/sports/features/columns/195992-pwr-live-holding-hands-while-wrestling-results-review |title=Grappling in the season of love: HHWW (Holding Hands While Wrestling) review |date=February 14, 2018| accessdate= April 16, 2018 | publisher= Rappler}}</ref> |pre1=yes |match1=John Sebastian defeated Kapitan PWR |stip1=[[Professional wrestling match types#Singles matches|Singles match]]; had Kapitan PWR won, he would have been the new PWR General Manager |pre2=yes |match2=Quatro and Trabajador Maximo def. Kakaibros (Kh3ndrick and Mh4rckie) |stip2=[[Professional wrestling match types#Tag team match|Tag team match]] |match3=SANDATA def. Jake de Leon |stip3=Singles match |match4=Bolt and Zayden Trudeau def. TDTxECX (Trian dela Torre and Evan Carleaux) |stip4=Tournament final tag team match to determine the #1 contenders to the PWR Tag Team Championship |match5=Vintendo def. Martivo |stip5=Singles match |match6=Crystal def. Robynn |stip6=[[Professional wrestling match types#Hardcore-based variations|All Out War Match]] |match7=PHX Champion Mike Madrigal, All Out War Champion Vlad Sinnsyk, and The Apocalypse def. Ken Warren and The YOLO Twins (Yohann and Logan Ollores) |stip7=Six-man tag team match |match8=PWR Tag Team Champions The Network (James "Idol" Martinez and Alexander Belmonte III) def. McKata and Brad Cruz |stip8=Non-title tag team match |match9=The Revo-Ranger def. Peter Versoza |stip9=Singles match |match10=Miguel Rosales def. PWR Champion Ralph Imabayashi and Rederick Mahaba |stip10=[[Professional wrestling match types#Handicap match|Handicap match]] |}}
