{{refimprove|date=June 2017}} {{Infobox music festival | name =MUTEK | image =File:Rhenke1.jpg | caption = | location =[[Montreal]], international | years_active =2000-present | founders = | dates = | genre = [[Electronic music]], [[experimental music]] | attendance = | capacity = | website = {{url|mutek.org}} }} '''MUTEK''' is a Montreal-based [[Music festival|festival]] dedicated to the promotion of [[electronic music]] and the digital arts.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Mertens|first1=Max|title=Montreal's Mutek Festival Turns 15|url=https://thump.vice.com/en_us/article/d7enmx/montreals-mutek-festival-turns-15|website=Vice|accessdate=2018-06-11|date=13 May 2014}}</ref> Its central platform is an annual five-day event in [[Montreal]] that takes place in late August.<ref>{{cite web |title=MUTEK Montreal moves to August, announces first names, including Zip and Daphni |url=https://www.residentadvisor.net/news.aspx?id=38549 |website=Resident Advisor |accessdate=6 June 2018}}</ref> Alongside the Montreal edition, MUTEK also hosts international versions of its festival.
==History== Mutek was founded in 2000 by Alain Mongeau.<ref>{{cite book|title=New York|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=pJMpAQAAIAAJ|year=2005|volume=39|publisher=[[New York Magazine]]}}</ref>
A Mexican edition of MUTEK has taken place in [[Mexico City]] since 2003. Annual South American single and/or multi-day events have taken place in [[Argentina]] and [[Chile]] since 2002 and 2004 respectively. Showcases have occurred in [[Brazil]] and [[Colombia]] as well.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mutek.org/en/about/coproductions | title=Summary of MUTEK Activities Outside Quebec | date=2016-12-20 | accessdate=2018-06-11}}</ref>{{Better source|date=June 2018}}
In 2005 MUTEK was among the first Western cultural organizations to send a delegation of electronic artists to [[China]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mutek.org/en/archives/events/2005/240-mutek_beijing | title=MUTEK_Beijing | date=2005 | accessdate=2018-06-11}}</ref>{{Better source|date=June 2018}}
In 2014, MUTEK paired with digital arts festival Elektra for the EM15 festival in Montreal.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Coultate|first1=Aaron|title=MUTEK and Elektra join forces for EM15|url=https://www.residentadvisor.net/news.aspx?id=23708|website=Resident Advisor|accessdate=2018-06-11|date=18 February 2014}}</ref>
